              </div>
              <div>
                <span class="text-sm text-red-600 font-medium">Lesson 05</span>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">The Dubai Drop: A 6-Sigma Event</h2>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- The Hook -->
            <div class="bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
              <p class="text-xl font-medium mb-2">Dubai's stock market dropped 6 standard deviations in 9 days.</p>
              <p class="text-xl font-medium text-red-400">A 1-in-1 billion event. It shouldn't happen once in the history of the universe.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- The Concept -->
            <div class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">The Concept</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
                Between February 28 and March 9, 2026, the Dubai Financial Market General Index (DFMGI) dropped <strong>14.1%</strong>. Using 5 years of historical data, this represents a <strong>6 standard deviation</strong> move.
              </p>
              <p class="text-slate-600">
                Under normal distribution assumptions, a 6-sigma event should occur roughly once every billion observations. Markets regularly produce these "impossible" events — because returns aren't normally distributed.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- The Data -->
            <div class="mb-8 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-4">The Numbers</h3>
              <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                <table class="w-full text-sm">
                  <thead>
                    <tr class="border-b border-slate-200">
                      <th class="text-left py-2 text-slate-500">Metric</th>
                      <th class="text-right py-2 text-slate-500">Value</th>
                    </tr>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody class="text-slate-700">
                    <tr class="border-b border-slate-100">
                      <td class="py-2">Historical 9-day mean</td>
                      <td class="text-right font-medium">+0.63%</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-slate-100">
                      <td class="py-2">Historical 9-day volatility (SD)</td>
                      <td class="text-right font-medium">2.45%</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-slate-100">
                      <td class="py-2">Feb 28 - Mar 9 return</td>
                      <td class="text-right font-medium text-red-600">-14.1%</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td class="py-2">Standard deviations</td>
                      <td class="text-right font-bold text-red-600">6.0 σ</td>
                    </tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
              </div>
              <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs mt-4">Note: Yahoo Finance data has gaps. Depending on NA handling, sigma ranges 5.5-6.5.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- What the R Code Proves -->
            <div class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">What the R Code Does</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                  </svg>
                  <span>Fetches 5 years of DFMGI.AE data from Yahoo Finance</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                  </svg>
                  <span>Computes rolling 9-day returns and historical volatility</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                  </svg>
                  <span>Calculates z-score and probability under normal distribution</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                  </svg>
                  <span>Visualizes the drop against the historical distribution</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Historical Context -->
            <div class="mb-8 bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-6">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">Fat Tails Are Features, Not Bugs</h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">Markets regularly produce "impossible" events:</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-700 text-sm">
                <li><strong>1987 Black Monday:</strong> 22 standard deviations</li>
                <li><strong>2008 Lehman collapse:</strong> Multiple 5+ sigma days</li>
                <li><strong>2020 COVID crash:</strong> 12 sigma single-day moves</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-slate-600 mt-4">
                If your risk model says "this can't happen," the market will prove it wrong.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Key Takeaway -->
            <div class="bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-emerald-800 mb-2">Key Takeaway</h3>
              <p class="text-emerald-700">
                <strong>Don't trust normal distribution for tail risk.</strong> Fat tails aren't anomalies — they're features of financial markets. Build portfolios that survive "impossible" events.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Download -->
            <div class="border-t border-slate-200 pt-6">
              <a
                href="/files/quant-r-lesson-05.R"
                download
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-red-100 text-red-700 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-red-200 transition-colors text-sm"
